configuration.title: Azure Machine Learning
CLI Compatibility Mode.description: Use commands and workflows compatible with the Azure Machine Learning 2.0 CLI. Change this setting to return to the previous 1.0 CLI flows.
experiments.enabled.description: Enables A/B tests in the Azure ML extension. If enabled, you may get included in proposed enhancements and/or features.
logging.level.description: The level of message the extension logs
showArchivedExperiments.description: Show archived experiments in the viewContext view and in quick-pick prompts.
workspaceFilter.description: Filter the list of workspaces as shown in the extension viewContext. Each key is a subscription ID and the value is a list of workspaces.
yaml.customTags.description: Custom tags for the parser to use
yaml.format.bracketSpacing: Print spaces between brackets in objects
yaml.format.printWidth.description: Specify the line length that the printer will wrap on
yaml.format.proseWrap.description: Always: wrap prose if it exceeds the print width, Never: never wrap the prose, Preserve: wrap prose as-is
yaml.format.singleQuote.description: Use single quotes instead of double quotes
yaml.schemas.description: Associate schemas to YAML files in the current workspace
yaml.schemaStore.enable.description: Automatically pull available YAML schemas from JSON Schema Store
yaml.trace.server.description: Traces the communication between Azure ML Extension and the Azure ML YAML language service.
